cards.rules:
Choose two (The choices must be different):
 +2 Cards;
 +2 Actions;
 +2 Coins;
 gain 4 Silvers and put your deck into your discard pile.
(This is not in the Supply.)

When you play this, choose one:
 +1 Buy and +2 Coins;
 or the next time you buy a card this turn, you may also gain a differently named card with the same cost.

Choose one:
 +3 Cards and a 1VP to the Wild Hunt Supply pile;
 or gain an Estate, and if you do, take the VP from the pile.

You may trash a Treasure from your hand. If you do, choose one:
 +2 Cards and +1 Action;
 or +2 Coins and +1 Buy.

Choose one:
 +2 Cards;
 or +2 Coins;
 or trash 2 cards from your hand.

+1 Action
Choose one; you get the version in parentheses:
 Each player gets +1 (+3) Cards;
 or each player gains a Silver (Gold);
 or each player may trash a card from his hand and gain a card costing exactly 1 Coin (2 Coins) more.

Choose one:
 Each other player reveals the top 2 cards of his deck, trashes a revealed Treasure that you choose, discards the rest, and if anyone trashed a Treasure you take a Coin token;
 or, +1 Coin per Coin token you've taken with Pirate Ships this game.

Reveal a card from your hand. For each type it has (Action, Attack, etc.), choose one: 

+1 Action; 
or +1 Buy; 
or +$3; 
or gain a Gold. 

The choices must be different.

If the number of cards you gained this turn is:
2+, gain an Imp from its pile;
1, gain a card costing up to $4;
0 gain a Gold.
